The president too!

73
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:04,680
Huh?

74
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:06,580
What are you doing in this place?

75
00:04:08,100 --> 00:04:09,320
Well, that's...

76
00:04:09,320 --> 00:04:10,740
You're hiding something.

77
00:04:11,900 --> 00:04:12,980
No, it's nothing.

78
00:04:13,340 --> 00:04:13,840
Liar!

79
00:04:14,280 --> 00:04:15,660
No, it's true.

80
00:04:17,060 --> 00:04:18,000
You're free to do whatever you want!

81
00:04:18,320 --> 00:04:18,780
I don't care!

82
00:04:34,380 --> 00:04:36,180
D-don't six!

83
00:04:41,080 --> 00:04:42,740
W-Water, water!

84
00:04:44,060 --> 00:04:46,220
Ugh... I'm saved...

85
00:04:47,060 --> 00:04:47,580
What?

86
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:50,640
Ryotsu, are you ready?

87
00:04:52,360 --> 00:04:53,560
S-sir!

88
00:04:57,760 --> 00:04:59,980
I'll never forgive you for this!

89
00:04:59,980 --> 00:05:01,060
You're fired!

90
00:05:01,820 --> 00:05:03,640
I understand your anger, sir!

91
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:06,820
But isn't firing too heavy a burden?

92
00:05:07,320 --> 00:05:09,680
If he's so bad-tempered...

93
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:12,480
If he's so bad-tempered, then it's all over!

94
00:05:13,180 --> 00:05:15,320
Anyway, Ohara, it's your responsibility!

95
00:05:15,940 --> 00:05:16,460
Huh?

96
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:19,680
You've been so spoiled all this time, so you can't do it!

97
00:05:20,100 --> 00:05:22,420
Hey, do you want to go shopping for the holidays?

98
00:05:22,420 --> 00:05:24,400
No, I can't!

99
00:05:25,060 --> 00:05:27,160
Please, I'll take care of it somehow!

100
00:05:30,540 --> 00:05:31,400
What?!

101
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:34,040
You're fired?!

102
00:05:34,860 --> 00:05:35,800
That's right.

103
00:05:36,060 --> 00:05:38,140
This month's salary will be cut by 50%!

104
00:05:39,620 --> 00:05:42,420
50% is half, isn't it?!

105
00:05:42,960 --> 00:05:44,060
That's not fair!

106
00:05:44,140 --> 00:05:44,920
It's not even cheap!

107
00:05:45,320 --> 00:05:47,680
If you cut 50% off, I can't live!

108
00:05:48,900 --> 00:05:49,860
I don't care!

109
00:05:49,980 --> 00:05:50,720
It's my own business!

110
00:05:51,180 --> 00:05:52,040
Can I be your father's cute husband?

111
00:05:54,140 --> 00:05:55,220
You're not cute!

112
00:05:55,520 --> 00:05:56,100
You're just a nuisance!

113
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:58,780
If I die, I'll go to the chief's place every day!

114
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:02,040
You can live by eating weeds!

115
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:05,200
Chief's demon!

116
00:06:06,940 --> 00:06:08,400
Yeah, I don't care if you're a demon or not!

117
00:06:09,300 --> 00:06:11,120
I'm tired of taking care of you!

118
00:06:12,540 --> 00:06:13,780
...or something like that.

119
00:06:13,780 --> 00:06:15,460
I think you'll have to pay for your own service.

120
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:18,120
You're right.

121
00:06:18,700 --> 00:06:20,500
I won't care if you're a good man or not!

122
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:25,480
What?!

123
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:26,800
Ryo-chan, you're saying too much!

124
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:28,280
Yes, I am, Senpai!

125
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:28,900
Heh!

126
00:06:29,340 --> 00:06:30,800
Anyway, I don't understand you, the men or women!

127
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:36,320
I'm not a man or a woman, but...

128
00:06:36,320 --> 00:06:37,140
You, keep quiet!

129
00:06:37,440 --> 00:06:37,800
I'll change my words!

130
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:39,620
I... I don't think so.

131
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:41,860
I don't think you're a chief, or a ohira!

132
00:06:43,180 --> 00:06:43,760
I don't think you're a chief, or a ohira!

133
00:06:43,760 --> 00:06:46,340
Enough! I don't think you're a subordinate!

134
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:55,640
Yes, yes! I'm at the exit in front of the park!

135
00:06:56,180 --> 00:06:57,300
Yes, yes!

136
00:06:58,200 --> 00:06:59,080
Um, Chief!

137
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:00,620
This is from my wife.

138
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:02,880
Ah, it's me.

139
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:05,200
I see! You were born!

140
00:07:06,880 --> 00:07:08,000
So, where's Hiromi?

141
00:07:10,010 --> 00:07:10,620
Tell me you're here.

142
00:07:10,620 --> 00:07:11,520
Tell me you're here.

143
00:07:12,540 --> 00:07:13,720
Chief, that was...

144
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:15,740
You have a granddaughter, huh?

145
00:07:16,060 --> 00:07:17,580
Ah, she's a girl this time.

146
00:07:17,740 --> 00:07:18,660
Wow! Congratulations!

147
00:07:19,640 --> 00:07:21,180
So, you're a family now?

148
00:07:21,980 --> 00:07:23,880
I was asked to think of a name for my daughter.

149
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:27,100
I thought about it a lot, but...

150
00:07:27,780 --> 00:07:28,460
How about Sakura?

151
00:07:29,900 --> 00:07:30,620
That's a good name!

152
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:32,060
Really?

153
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:33,360
I-I guess so.

154
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:35,660
That's strange!

155
00:07:36,340 --> 00:07:38,120
The eldest son is Daisuke, right?

156
00:07:38,220 --> 00:07:40,580
If the eldest is Daisuke, the youngest is Hanako, right?

157
00:07:40,620 --> 00:07:42,380
Then, it's a manzai duo.

158
00:07:42,980 --> 00:07:44,880
Otherwise, the eldest is Torajirou, right?

159
00:07:45,960 --> 00:07:46,800
Isn't it Torasan?

160
00:07:47,520 --> 00:07:50,620
You should change your last name to Hayashiya, Pei, and Paako.

161
00:07:50,980 --> 00:07:51,880
Ryo-chan!

162
00:07:52,180 --> 00:07:52,920
Well, well.

163
00:07:52,980 --> 00:07:54,500
I don't have time to fight such an idiot.

164
00:07:55,960 --> 00:07:58,100
Anyway, when Hiromi is discharged, I'll prepare a feast.

165
00:07:59,080 --> 00:08:00,060
Come and see your grandchildren.

166
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:02,420
Huh? A feast?

167
00:08:03,120 --> 00:08:04,560
It has nothing to do with you.

168
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:05,460
You're not my subordinate.

169
00:08:06,780 --> 00:08:07,620
I know!

170
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:09,640
After all, they're all newborn babies.

171
00:08:10,620 --> 00:08:11,780
They all look like monkeys.

172
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:13,440
It's not interesting at all.

173
00:08:15,860 --> 00:08:16,760
Oh, right.

174
00:08:16,820 --> 00:08:17,580
I'd like to see you next Sunday.

175
00:08:18,320 --> 00:08:20,540
There's a fireworks festival in the neighborhood.

176
00:08:20,540 --> 00:08:21,520
It looks good from the garden of my house.

177
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:23,860
That's nice.

178
00:08:24,280 --> 00:08:25,440
I'm glad to see you.

179
00:08:25,860 --> 00:08:27,880
I have to think of something for the celebration.

180
00:08:29,360 --> 00:08:30,520
Don't worry about it.

181
00:08:30,980 --> 00:08:32,500
I'll tell you I was asked to do it.

182
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:35,640
But half the salary is hard.

183
00:08:36,040 --> 00:08:37,240
I have to do something about it.

184
00:08:44,940 --> 00:08:45,440
But I don't have time to do it.

185
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:46,060
A part-time job?

186
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:46,800
Ryo-chan?

187
00:08:47,460 --> 00:08:47,960
Right.

188
00:08:48,180 --> 00:08:50,760
In this season, there are fireworks events all over the place.

189
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:51,000
So, it's time to start.

190
00:08:51,880 --> 00:08:54,060
I want to work there, too.

191
00:08:54,060 --> 00:08:54,360
Right?

192
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:55,360
I'm in trouble with my salary being reduced.

193
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:57,500
Right? Right?

194
00:08:57,880 --> 00:09:00,200
Well, things that are too busy are too busy.

195
00:09:00,880 --> 00:09:02,340
Anyway, it's a dangerous job.

196
00:09:03,020 --> 00:09:04,320
Even if you call it a part-time job.

197
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:05,840
I'm experienced.

198
00:09:06,940 --> 00:09:08,680
Have you ever made a fireworks?

199
00:09:08,680 --> 00:09:12,400
There's no fireworks but I'm a veteran of explosions

200
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:14,000
You can't blow up

201
00:09:14,820 --> 00:09:17,260
But explosions and fireworks are the same

202
00:09:17,260 --> 00:09:20,320
It's not the same even if you use a gun

203
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:25,340
The fireworks are an art of the sky made by craftsmen

204
00:09:25,340 --> 00:09:28,820
This is the handmade fireworks

205
00:09:29,580 --> 00:09:34,000
Red, green and blue will change to three colors while the fireworks are burning

206
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:35,560
It looks like a fireball

207
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:37,500
It's like a fireball

208
00:09:37,500 --> 00:09:41,860
Many stars in the fireworks will change colors and fly in all directions

209
00:09:41,860 --> 00:09:46,540
But they won't be the same if you just fly

210
00:09:46,540 --> 00:09:49,380
It won't look good if you fly in circles

211
00:09:49,380 --> 00:09:51,400
So you have to line up like this

212
00:09:53,420 --> 00:09:57,900
You have to calculate the colors and make the stars

213
00:09:57,900 --> 00:10:02,600
I see, it's a craftsmanship

214
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:03,840
Right

215
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:07,040
That's why people with a rough personality won't like it

216
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:09,200
I'm a rare face

217
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:10,560
You can tell by my face

218
00:10:10,560 --> 00:10:13,620
I have a license to handle dangerous objects

219
00:10:13,620 --> 00:10:17,560
And I became a veteran because of the fireworks

220
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:19,580
Of course

221
00:10:19,580 --> 00:10:23,900
If you help people while you're alive, you'll be fine

222
00:10:24,610 --> 00:10:26,980
Don't kill me easily

223
00:10:26,980 --> 00:10:29,280
I trained my son so I can give him a reward

224
00:10:29,670 --> 00:10:30,940
I told you to stop

225
00:10:30,940 --> 00:10:32,780
I can't help it

226
00:10:32,780 --> 00:10:34,460
I did it, will you hire me?

227
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:50,640
Ryo, you got a lot better

228
00:10:50,640 --> 00:10:52,020
You're right

229
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:55,040
I have an idea for a new fireworks

230
00:10:56,020 --> 00:10:57,740
A new fireworks?

231
00:10:58,020 --> 00:10:59,060
I'll give you an idea

232
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:01,040
It's a huge hit

233
00:11:05,220 --> 00:11:05,740
The last firework

234
00:11:05,740 --> 00:11:07,620
Like this, the last firework had to be lit with candles.

235
00:11:09,980 --> 00:11:13,240
This is troublesome, and the candle light disappears in the wind.

236
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:17,640
This is what we improved and made it compatible with matches.

237
00:11:19,100 --> 00:11:21,860
When you light a fire, it becomes a flash fire.

238
00:11:22,740 --> 00:11:26,040
In a ski resort, you can turn this into a torch and do a night ski.

239
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:28,020
You can take this.

240
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:36,180
I failed a little earlier, but this time I'm fine.

241
00:11:37,520 --> 00:11:40,760
This is a giant snake firework. It's called a "Taija firework."

242
00:11:41,560 --> 00:11:42,840
This one is a big deal!

243
00:11:47,140 --> 00:11:50,200
This time, it's fine. It's a "Message firework."

244
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:51,640
A "Message firework"?

245
00:11:51,640 --> 00:11:55,080
A machine with a fluorescent diode is placed inside the firework.

246
00:11:55,780 --> 00:11:56,940
You can send a message to the fluorescent diode.

247
00:11:58,580 --> 00:12:00,240
When it explodes, it will open.

248
00:12:01,560 --> 00:12:05,120
When the fireworks are lit, a message will appear in the night sky.

249
00:12:06,640 --> 00:12:09,560
That's amazing! If that's true, it's a big hit!

250
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:14,640
By the way, this prototype is called "Banzai."

251
00:12:14,640 --> 00:12:16,020
Let's give it a try!

252
00:12:20,520 --> 00:12:21,620
There was a lot of firewood.

253
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:24,120
This is no good.

254
00:12:25,440 --> 00:12:25,880
"Banzai"

255
00:12:30,380 --> 00:12:30,860
"Banzai"

256
00:12:30,860 --> 00:12:31,320
Thanks for the good service!

257
00:12:33,060 --> 00:12:35,120
Miyasako, is this a picture of your grandchild?

258
00:12:36,020 --> 00:12:36,500
Yes.

259
00:12:37,320 --> 00:12:39,820
Isn't it cute? How many have you got?

260
00:12:40,500 --> 00:12:41,260
I've got three this year.

261
00:12:42,040 --> 00:12:43,120
It's almost my birthday.

262
00:12:43,680 --> 00:12:44,880
I'm thinking of giving her a gift.

263
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:48,960
Is your grandchild really that cute?

264
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:51,420
You bet it is!

265
00:12:52,240 --> 00:12:54,060
Just looking at the picture gives me the energy.

266
00:12:55,880 --> 00:12:57,720
I don't even have a grandchild or a wife.

267
00:12:59,740 --> 00:13:03,660
Actually, right after she was born, the company I founded had to go bankrupt.

268
00:13:05,160 --> 00:13:10,820
I was already very happy, but when I saw my newborn grandchild's smile, I felt that I had to work hard.

269
00:13:12,600 --> 00:13:13,900
So you came here.

270
00:13:14,420 --> 00:13:16,360
Yes. I've been dating the president here since I was a kid.

271
00:13:18,580 --> 00:13:20,680
After all, my grandchild is the source of my energy.

